          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the batter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk the flour, yeast, sugar, and salt together. Add the warm water and whisk to a smooth, thick batter, the consistency of thick double cream. Cover and rest at room temperature for 1 hour until the batter is bubbly and has risen visibly.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fry",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oil in a large saucepan to 180°C. Using two wet dessertspoons, scoop a heaped spoonful of batter and use the second spoon to push it off into the oil. Each should be roughly the size of a ping-pong ball. Fry in batches of 6 to 8, turning continuously with a slotted spoon, for 3 to 4 minutes until deep amber all over. They will self-round as they cook. Drain briefly.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Serve",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pile the hot loukoumades into a bowl. Drizzle the warm honey over liberally, scatter the crushed walnuts, and dust with cinnamon. Serve within 5 minutes. They lose their crunch quickly.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
